TITLE: Red state hunts Tren de Aragua terrorists as judges light ‘credibility on fire’ fighting deportations: senator
SUMMARY: Tennessee officials are working to combat members of Tren de Aragua, a Venezuelan gang, as left-leaning officials push back on deportations of illegal immigrants.

TITLE: Ohio grandmother mauled to death by pit bulls while ‘peacefully gardening’: lawsuit
SUMMARY: A newly-filed lawsuit claims that the pit bulls responsible for fatally attacking an Ohio grandmother last year had gotten into a stash of cocaine weeks prior to the tragic event.

TITLE: Harvard offers free tuition to students whose families make $200K or less per year
SUMMARY: On Monday, Harvard University announced it is expanding its financial aid program and offering free tuition to students whose families make $200,000 a year or less.

TITLE: Delta plane wing clips runway during botched landing at LaGuardia Airport
SUMMARY: The wing of a Delta plane struck the runway as it was landing at LaGuardia Airport on Sunday evening, according to the Federal Aviation Administration.

TITLE: Missing American college student seen in new hotel security footage before disappearance
SUMMARY: Missing University of Pittsburgh student Sudiksha Konanki is seen in recently released security camera footage from the hotel where she was staying in the Dominican Republic.

TITLE: Missing American in Dominican Republic: Key witness asks court to end de facto house arrest
SUMMARY: American Joshua Riibe files writ of habeas corpus, seeking release from 'irregular' detention in Punta Cana amid search for UPitt spring breaker Sudiksha Konanki.

TITLE: USPS worker convicted of stealing $1.6 million in checks, then spending it on luxury hotels, gentlemen's clubs
SUMMARY: A former U.S. Postal Service worker was convicted of stealing around $1.6 million in checks to fund "stays at luxury hotels" and "purchases at gentlemen’s clubs," federal prosecutors said.

TITLE: Fani Willis ordered to pay $54K for violating open records laws in Trump case
SUMMARY: Judge Rachel Krause has ordered District Attorney Fani Willis to pay more than $54,000 in relation to the RICO case of then-former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Scott Peterson attacked in California prison by fellow murderer: corrections dept
SUMMARY: Scott Peterson was attacked in prison by fellow California murderer Charles Miles, corrections officials said. Peterson was convicted of killing his pregnant wife, Laci.

TITLE: Columbine shooting survivor loses battle with cancer
SUMMARY: Karissa Rund, a Colorado woman who survived the Columbine High School shooting more than 25 years ago, passed away following a battle with cancer.

TITLE: California mom's disappearance now a homicide case as detectives eye persons of interest
SUMMARY: The May 2024 disappearance of California mom Nikki Cheng Saelee-McCain is now being investigated as a homicide based on evidence recently discovered by detectives.

TITLE: Roof collapses at St. Patrick's Day party near University of Pittsburgh, dozens injured
SUMMARY: Dozens were injured after a partial roof collapse on Friday during a St. Patrick's Day celebration near the University of Pittsburgh.

TITLE: Stranded astronauts prepare for long-awaited return to Earth
SUMMARY: Astronauts Butch Wilmore and Suni Williams could be back on Earth as early as Tuesday, if all goes as planned for their return from space after nine months.

TITLE: Turks and Caicos travel warning issued as migrants descend on popular vacation spot in droves
SUMMARY: Migrants, crime and a Level 2 travel advisory from the U.S. State Department have raised concerns about traveling to Turks and Caicos, a popular vacation destination for Americans.

TITLE: Trump responds after judge tries to stop deportation flights with violent gangbangers and more top headlines
SUMMARY: Get all the stories you need-to-know from the most powerful name in news delivered first thing every morning to your inbox.

TITLE: Legal fight over American college student’s resort disappearance could come down to who was ‘reckless’: lawyer
SUMMARY: The disappearance of an American college student in the Dominican Republic has prompted questions about liability that the resort where she was staying could potentially face.

TITLE: University of Wisconsin-Madison's ex-diversity officer scrutinized over spending, judgment amid DEI crackdown
SUMMARY: The University of Wisconsin-Madison's former chief diversity officer displayed a "significant lapse" in judgment and fiscal responsibility, according to an internal report.

TITLE: Sanctuary city lawyers plot to help illegal migrants evade ICE in exposed group email
SUMMARY: Leaked emails to and from certain Minneapolis-area lawyers show efforts to actively thwart efforts from ICE to apprehend illegal immigrant defendants in the sanctuary city.

TITLE: Friends of Joshua Riibe, witness in case of missing American student, say the community 'stands behind' him
SUMMARY: A key witness in the case of missing American student Sudiksha Konanki has the support of his community, according to friends of his family.

TITLE: Trump sends National Guard to tornado-ravaged Arkansas as 37 deaths reported across multiple states
SUMMARY: President Donald Trump has activated the National Guard in tornado-struck Arkansas after storms ripped through multiple states over the weekend, leaving at least 37 dead.

TITLE: Washington girl, 4, ‘dragged’ by coyote just inches from door amid string of alarming encounters: report
SUMMARY: A 4-year-old Washington girl was "dragged" by a coyote just inches from the front door of her home on March 11, her father told local news, in a string of recent coyote encounters.

TITLE: Report: Jewish Tesla owner 'speechless' after Jewish Musk-hater finger-traces swastika on his Cybertruck
SUMMARY: A Jewish man was "speechless" after reportedly seeing an Elon Musk protester draw a swastika on his Cybertruck in NYC. The incident comes amid a wave of anti-DOGE protests in the U.S.

TITLE: Man set on fire in heart of New York City's Times Square, suspect at large: report
SUMMARY: Police in New York City are actively searching for an unidentified male suspect who lit a man on fire overnight Sunday in in the middle of Times Square.

TITLE: American tourist causes international outrage after posting wombat video
SUMMARY: U.S.-based influencer Sam Jones faced widespread criticism on social media after posting a video in which she took a baby wombat from its mother and filmed the animal's reactions.

TITLE: Missing Connecticut girl found alive 25 years after kidnapping with help from DNA testing
SUMMARY: Police in New Haven, Connecticut, have identified and located a missing girl after her mother abducted her 25 years ago and brought her to Mexico in 1999.
